{
  "stem": "15962.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then, as the Russian Front advanced in December and January from the east, the Germans were sending more and more [BACKROUND NOISE] people to the West, to the-- to the German heartland, to liquidate the camps, to leave-- try and eradicate the evidence of what they have created.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Late in 1944, they stopped using the gas chambers and the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And shortly before everybody left, they actually blew up a couple of the crematoria and gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was still working as a messenger, to the best of my memory.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But as winter intensified and the Front advanced, more and more people were being sent out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a panic, and fear, that those who will stay behind will all be shot.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And indeed, only-- eventually, only the very, very-- the people who just couldn't move were left behind.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the person who was later my guardian was one of them who was left there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because he injured both his feet and couldn't-- couldn't even get out of his bed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We-- in a hurry one night, we were all herded together and sent out in-- in groups into the night.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was very, very cold.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because I had a job that had access to clothing, I had reasonably serviceable shoes, whereas many of the prisoners had wooden shoes.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They had no socks and were ill-equipped for the freezing night and-- and the snow.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The death march started somewhat disorganized.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there were-- as I said, we were sent out in groups and--",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They didn't tell us anything.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had no idea where we were going, how long we'll be going.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Here and there, I would find or be together with somebody I knew from this group.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
